cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on mobile computation offloading and its impact on radio-access networks, which falls under the purview of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a novel technique for integrating task-level computation prediction and prefetching within the cloud-computing process of a large program with numerous tasks, which involves distributed computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper applies stochastic optimization to design online-fetching policies to minimize mobile energy consumption under a deadline constraint, which falls under the purview of systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper models the tasks in an offloaded program as a stochastic sequence and applies stochastic optimization to design online-fetching policies, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper leverages prediction to reduce the program runtime and mobile transmission energy, which involves machine learning techniques.
